.cs 4 on
.item 'SHOW PERMITS Command' 'Updated on 11/26/84 by AEH'
.boxon
SHOW PERMITS [ACCOUNT gg.uuu|filename\[account-options]]
.*           <-------------> <------> <---------------->
.* FIELD COMMAND HEL SHO PERM ACCOUNT gg.uuu
.* FIELD COMMAND HEL SHO PERM filename
.* FIELD COMMAND HEL SHO PERM account-options
             [FOR\{account|PUBLIC}]
.*           <-------------------->
.* FIELD COMMAND HEL SHO PERM FOR account PUBLIC
.boxoff

.* DESCRIPTION
The SHOW PERMITS command displays the ORVYL file access privileges set for a
specified account or file.

The SHOW PERMITS command with a filename displays the file access privileges
set for that account.  With the ACCOUNT option, the SHOW PERMITS command
displays the users who have access to all files belonging to the specified
account, or the account-level file permits.

If neither option is given, the SHOW PERMITS command displays the
account-level permits set for the logged-on account.

If "FOR ..." is specified, then only the permits for the specified
user, GROUP, or PUBLIC are displayed.

.* SELECT 'SHOW PERMIT Command Options'
.us Options Descriptions

.* OPTION ACCOUNT
.optix ACCOUNT
ACCOUNT gg.uuu\\\\\an account for which the access privileges are
                   to be displayed.

.* OPTION filename
.optix filename
filename\\\\\\\\\\\the particular ORVYL file for which the access privileges
                   are to be displayed.

.* OPTION account-options
.optix account-options
account-options\\\\specify an ORVYL file belonging to an account other than
                   the logged-on user.  One form of this option is
                   ACCOUNT gg.uuu.  Type HELP ACCOUNT OPTIONS for a
                   description of the account options.

.* OPTION FOR account,public
                   account displays the access level assigned to a user or
                   group of users to the specified file or account.  This
                   options may be in the form gg.uuu, GROUP gg, or USER uuu.

\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\PUBLIC displays the access-level assigned to the public
                   for the specified account or ORVYL file.

.cs 4 off

